A major problem in controlling the COVID-19 pandemic is the emergence of asymptomatic carriers who act as silent spreaders of the virus.40,41 Reports show that about 40% of infected individuals are asymptomatic.42,43 In our KMC-CA simulation, we provide probability (Pasym), which decides whether an infected individual will be asymptomatic (A) or not. The probability is determined by the percentage of the infected population that develops no symptoms.44 Initially, a random asymptomatic index (\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
