In each step of the simulation, an I can either remain infected of recover or die. This is determined by the following probabilities:
PI : This determines whether the concerned I remains infected or not. This is proportional to the incubation period of the virus and the time period for which a person remains infected. We find that for a disease like SARS-CoV-2 to persist in a society this probability needs to be very high (PI > 0.9).
\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$P_{I \to C}^{Res}$$\end{document}PI→CRes: This gives the probability of recovery of a resilient I.
\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
